  "text": "where b(t) and y(t) represent the input and output of the models at time t, respectively. The lag of the system is d, and f is a nonlinear function representing the ANN [CITATION_1] . The goal of the network is to learn associations (weights and bias values) between the set of input-output pairs. Because the neural network is small, the weights and bias values are updated using the Levenberg-Marquardt optimization because it is computationally efficient and converges quickly [CITATION_2] .",
